Oversigt over Tell Fisks køb af fisk (Netværksanalyse)¶

Dette afsnit har fokus p en dataekslorativ tilgang, hvor Tell Fisks mest indkbte fisketyper findes, hvilkelt danner grundlag for den videre analyse.

In [5]:
network = df[['Art', 'Sort', 'Total']]
network.columns = ['Art', 'Sort', 'Total_pris']
network["Fisk+Sort"] = network["Art"].astype(str) + network["Sort"].astype(str)
network = network.assign(target=(network['Fisk+Sort']).astype('category').cat.codes)
network['source'] = 128

In [7]:
total = network[['Total_pris', 'target']]
total = total.groupby('target')['Total_pris'].sum().reset_index()
In [8]:
fisk = network[['target', 'Fisk+Sort']]
fisk = fisk.groupby(['Fisk+Sort']).mean().reset_index()
In [9]:
edges = network[['source', 'target']]
edges = edges.groupby(['source','target']).size().reset_index()
edges.rename({0:'Antal_kb'}, axis=1, inplace=True)
edges.sort_values('Antal_kb', ascending=False)

new_row = {'source':128, 'target':128}

In [12]:
note_attr = edges.set_index('target').to_dict('index')
edgelist = list(zip(edges.source, edges.target, edges.Antal_kb))

g = nx.Graph()
degree_dict = dict(g.degree(g.nodes()))

g.add_weighted_edges_from(edgelist)
nx.set_node_attributes(g, note_attr)
g.nodes(data=True)

In [14]:

labels = hv.Labels(g_plot.nodes, ['x', 'y'], 'Fisk+Sort')
from holoviews.operation.datashader import datashade, bundle_graph
bundled = bundle_graph(g_plot)

show(hv.render(bundled*labels.opts(text_font_size='10pt', text_color='black',  bgcolor='lightgray')))

FBProphet har den mulighed at man kan fjerne weekender og dermed undg stj. Dette gres nedenfor.

In [60]:
prophet.set_index('ds', inplace=True)
prophet = prophet[prophet.index.dayofweek < 5].reset_index()

fig = go.Figure()

fig.add_trace(go.Scatter(x=prophet['ds'], y=prophet['y'], name='Gnsn.',))
fig.show()

For at anvende dataene i analysen skal de frst tranformeres til en normalfordeling med box cox vrktjet.

In [61]:
prophet['y'], lam = boxcox(prophet['y'])
print('Lambda is:', lam)

Lambda is: -0.5732127070330892

For at optimere modellen anvendes gridsearch til at forbedre de enkelte parametre.


De forskellige parametre som er afprvet er:


'changepoint_range': [0.6, 0.7, 0.75, 0.8, 0.9],


'changepoint_prior_scale': [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5],


'seasonality_prior_scale':[0.5, 1.0, 2.5, 5],


'yearly_seasonality':[5, 10, 15, 20],


'weekly_seasonality':[5, 10, 15, 20],













In [70]:



    


def create_param_combinations(**param_dict):
    param_iter = itertools.product(*param_dict.values())
    params =[]
    for param in param_iter:
        params.append(param) 
    params_df = pd.DataFrame(params, columns=list(param_dict.keys()))
    return params_df

def single_cv_run(history_df, metrics, param_dict, parallel):
    m = Prophet(**param_dict)
    m.add_regressor('Kilo', standardize=False)
    m.fit(history_df)
    df_cv = cross_validation(m, horizon='100 days')
    df_p = performance_metrics(df_cv, rolling_window=1)
    df_p['params'] = str(param_dict)
    df_p = df_p.loc[:, metrics]
    return df_p

# Oversigt over de forskellige parametre der er afprvet:
#'changepoint_range': [0.6, 0.7, 0.75, 0.8, 0.9],
#'changepoint_prior_scale': [0.01, 0.05, 0.1, 0.25, 0.5],
#'seasonality_prior_scale':[0.5, 1.0, 2.5, 5],
#'yearly_seasonality':[5, 10, 15, 20],
#'weekly_seasonality':[5, 10, 15, 20],


pd.set_option('display.max_colwidth', None)
param_grid = {  'changepoint_range': [0.3],
                'changepoint_prior_scale': [0.01],
                'seasonality_prior_scale':[3],
                'yearly_seasonality':[20],
                'weekly_seasonality':[5],
              }
metrics = ['horizon', 'rmse', 'mae', 'mape', 'mdape','params'] 
results = []

#Prophet(,)
params_df = create_param_combinations(**param_grid)
for param in params_df.values:
    param_dict = dict(zip(params_df.keys(), param))
    cv_df = single_cv_run(prophet,  metrics, param_dict, parallel="processes")
    results.append(cv_df)
results_df = pd.concat(results).reset_index(drop=True)
best_param = results_df.loc[results_df['rmse'] == min(results_df['rmse']), ['params']]
print(f'\n The best param combination is {best_param.values[0][0]}')
